cn:association.cn:title: Dow rises more than 150 points as Wal-Mart and Cisco jump after earnings
cn:association.cn:summary: U.S. equities rose on Thursday, rebounding from consecutive declines, following strong quarterly results from Cisco Systems and Wal-Mart.
cn:association.cn:linkHeadline: Dow rises more than 150 points as Wal-Mart and Cisco jump after earnings
cn:association.headline: Dow rises more than 150 points as Wal-Mart and Cisco jump after earnings
cn:association.cn:shorterHeadline: Dow rises more than 150 points as Wal-Mart and Cisco jump after earnings
cn:association.cn:shorterDescription: U.S. equities rose on Thursday, rebounding from consecutive declines, following strong quarterly results from Cisco Systems and Wal-Mart.
cn:association.cn:shortestDescription: Stocks rose, rebounding from consecutive declines, following strong quarterly results from Cisco Systems and Wal-Mart.
cn:association.cn:bodyTeaser:
U.S. equities rose on Thursday, rebounding from consecutive declines, following strong quarterly results from Cisco Systems and Wal-Mart. Wall Street also looked ahead to a key vote on tax reform.

The Dow Jones industrial average gained more than 150 points, with Cisco and Wal-Mart leading advancers on the 30-stock index.

Wal-Mart reported better-than-expected quarterly earnings and revenue, sending the stock more than 8 percent higher to an all-time high. The company's results were boosted by a surge in grocery and online sales.

"Overall the F3Q result suggests investments continue to favorably impact comp growth and shows Walmart is effectively competing in a tough retail environment," Mark Astrachan, an analyst at Stifel, said in a note.

Cisco also reported earnings and revenue that beat Wall Street expectations, lifted in part by strong sales of software applications. Cisco shares popped 6 percent and were on track for their best session since Feb. 11, 2016.
